    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Fuel System - Installation -
        High-Pressure Oil Pump
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="5">
        <title>High-Pressure Oil Pump</title>
        <figure id="f2651231" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh09/H09059.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>IPR valve assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring seal #015 (green)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Back-up ring seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring seal #016 (green)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">IPR valve assembly</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new O-rings onto IPR valve assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651232" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh11/H11054.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the IPR valve assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f2651234" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH11/H11052.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>IPR orientation</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fitting assembly, M18</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 100 (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 30 (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f2651234.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH11/H11058.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Installing the IPR valve</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the IPR valve into the high-pressure pump assembly finger tight. Use the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_250.xml" xrefid="t2651203" appearance="hottext">IPR removal / installation
                    tool
                </hotlnk>
                and a torque wrench to tighten IPR valve to the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_249.xml" xrefid="t2651202" appearance="hottext">special torque value</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use petroleum jelly to hold a new O-ring gasket into the recessed groove, located on the
                backside of the front cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position high-pressure oil pump making sure gear meshes with upper idler gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two bolts (M8 x 100) behind pump and two bolts (M8 x 30) outside, securing the
                high-pressure pump to the front cover. Tighten bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_249.xml" xrefid="t2651202" appearance="hottext">special torque value</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651235" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh11/H11031.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Installing the high-pressure oil hose</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-ring seal onto the high-pressure pump assembly before installing the
                high-pressure hose assembly. Tighten swivel nut by hand.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-ring seal onto the high-pressure fitting (M18) at the cylinder head prior to
                installing the high-pressure hose assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Orient hose fitting assembly towards the front of engine at 0&#176;&#177; 7&#176; relative
                to horizontal. Tighten swivel nut by hand.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a crowfoot, tighten both swivel nuts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_249.xml" xrefid="t2651202" appearance="hottext">special torque value</hotlnk>
                making sure hose is not under any excess tension.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
